# Responsible: Loy 

!!! PUT USB STICK IN AMIGO3 !!!

Environment:
In rosed challenge_emergency emergency.py (search for 'manipulation_location'), look up where each object should be placed. 

amigo2:

    hardware: base, spindle, left-arm, head
    
amigo1:
    in rsettings, enable 3dnav:
        "export AMIGO_NAV=3d"
    and source ~/.bashrc in the terminal you launch amiddle from.
    amiddle

amigo3:

    pumount --yes-I-really-want-lazy-unmount /media/usb-stick/
    (Don't worry if this gives errors)

    # Check the drive letter of the usb device (the highest letter/number combi)
    ls /dev/sd*
 
    # Mount the usb stick (for example: /dev/sdc1)
    pmount /dev/sdb{???}1 usb-stick #This must *NOT* give errors, or the emergency_paper thingy will crash on startup

    #Check whether the USB stick is properly mounted
    ls /media/usb-stick #Should not give errors

    roslaunch challenge_emergency emergency_home_dependencies.launch #Must also *NOT* crash or segfault. There may be some params missing, no biggie.
amigo3:
    (You can store and restore alsamixer settings with 'sudo alsactl store 0' and 'sudo alsactl restore 0', where 0 is the sound card number)
    alsamixer
        Mic Boost -> 22
        Capture -> 44
        Digital -> 29
        Mic on mute!!! (Should be muted already)
        
    reset-audio
    amigo-console        
        test_audio

    rosrun challenge_emergency emergency.py

SCENARIO:
	Please see the rulebook (https://docs.google.com/viewer?a=v&pid=sites&srcid=cm9ib2N1cGF0aG9tZS5vcmd8cm9ib2N1cC1ob21lfGd4OjEzYWQ0MzQwYjdhYmQyODM) page 48 & 49.
	- A person may be wandering about in the designated room (hardcoded in the top of emergency.py)
	- Between 30 and 60 seconads after the start, the person has an accident.
	- After the accident, the person is sitting or lying on the ground or sitting in a chair.
        - Amigo has the find the person and asks a few questions. One question is to bring something. The options are water, cellphone and first aid kit. 

After the challenge ended, you can inspect the PDF by either getting the USB stick from amigo, or by running:
 amigo@athomeX $ scp amigo@amigo3:/media/usb-stick/emergency_paper.pdf . ; evince emergency_paper.pdf
---------------------------------------

Dependency launch file includes:
- including paramaters.yaml in emergency package
- running virtual_cam for starting service to get picture
